        WEEKLY CHART REVIEW (18/09/2020 - 24/09/2020)

        (Negative)

        1) Mood mightve closed the gap on Wap again today, but it still wasnt enough to go #1 this week. At least Ireland know what theyre doing, as the former managed to overtake there today!

        2) I knew this was going to happen, but Take You Dancing is now a Top 10 hit! I can only hope its sudden loss of momentum means that it wont be here for long.

        3) Not only that, but the song its replacing is Greece, which Ive really started liking this week! Typical, isnt it?

        4) Both Juice WRLD songs have both gone on ACR! Im mixed on Juice WRLD as an artist in general, but both Wishing Well & especially Come & Go are among the best hits of his entire discography.

        5) Cardigan didnt return! Based on how much airplay it got from Radio 1 this week, I really thought it would come back.

        6) A sixth negative the most Ive done in a traffic light review so far! This time its because Folklore didnt return to the Top 5 of the albums chart, while the early BuzzJack numbers were indicating that it might.

        (Mixed)

        1) Loose is the highest debut of the week, even if it did drop a lot from both updates! Im not all that surprised though. Its not bad, but unfortunately, it doesnt come close to Rover for me!

        2) Im warming to Lemonade slightly, but I just feel more indifferent than annoyed by it now! Still, with a climb of 20 places, itll probably re-enter the Top 10 next week anyway.

        3) Dance Monkey re-entered the Top 40 & its now one week away from spending an entire year in the region! On one hand, the radio are still way too obsessed with playing this, but on the other hand, at least I absolutely loved the song back when it was ruling the charts.

        4) Obey dropped massively! I knew this was coming given that metal has little or no longevity on the charts, but I think a lot of regulars here, e.g. Coolocelot & George, are going to be just fine with it leading, haha.

        5) Doves got the #1 on the albums chart by a massive margin! Once again, I havent got around to hearing it yet, but Ive heard from a couple of people on here that its meant to be really enjoyable, so I might check it out next week at some point.

        (Positive)

        1) The only positive point I can really mention as far as the upper reaches of the chart go is that Looking For Me is now a Top 5 hit. It looks like it might be the highest charting dance hit by next week, which is a very promising sign!

        2) While Ill be extremely disappointed if it doesnt get there, Im excited to see You Broke Me First just hovering beneath the Top 10 & that it could break into the region at any time.

        3) Giants actually moved up again this week, becoming Dermot Kennedys second Top 20! Its always satisfying to see an underrated artist finally getting another hit & Id like to see Outnumbered-level success for this one too.

        4) While Lasting Lover might be a non-mover, I was expecting it to drop a lot this week, so that shows much radio are getting on board with this awesome EDM banger!

        5) Tap In becomes Saweeties first charting entry! Lots of female rappers have been making huge breakthroughs in 2020, but Im really pleased that this song passed through all the competition. Saweetie brings an energetic & charismatic flow, the underlying beat is really prominent & that hook is incredibly addictive! In a week where weve got an underwhelming song trying to do the same thing at #1, we really needed this. I hope well be hearing more of this in the coming weeks!

        Overall, yeah, between having a day filled with panic attacks & the news only further adding to my depression, I really could've done without such an underwhelming chart today! Oh well, theres always next week.

        Enjoy your weekend everybody! :)

        JB
